4 (3) Five members shall represent the public, who may not be active or
5 retired judges, who are not admitted to practice law in this State, and who may not have a
6 financial relationship with or receive compensation from a judge or a person admitted to
7 practice law in this State.
8 (4) The composition of the Commission should reflect the race, gender, and
9 geographic diversity of the population of the State.
