11 THE term of office of each member is four years commencing on January 1 following the
12 expiration of the member’s predecessor’s term. A member may not serve more than two
13 four–year terms, or for more than a total of ten years if appointed to fill a vacancy.
14 (e) A member’s membership automatically terminates:
15 (1) When any member of the Commission appointed from among judges in
16 the State ceases to be a judge;
17 (2) When any member appointed from among those admitted to practice
18 law becomes a judge;
19 (3) When any member representing the public becomes a judge or is
20 admitted to the practice of law in this State or has a financial relationship with or receives
21 compensation from a judge or a person admitted to practice law in this State; or
22 (4) When any member ceases to be a resident of the State.
23 (f) Any vacancies on the Commission shall be filled for the unexpired term by the
24 Governor in the same manner as for making of appointments to the Commission and
25 subject to the same qualifications which were applicable to the person causing the vacancy.
26 (g) A member of the Commission may not receive any compensation for the
27 member’s services as such but shall be allowed any expenses necessarily incurred in the
28 performance of the member’s duties as such member.
29 4B.
30 (a) (1) The Commission on Judicial Disabilities has the power to:
31 (i) Investigate complaints against any justice or judge of the
32 Supreme Court of Maryland, any intermediate courts of appeal, the circuit courts, the
33 District Court of Maryland, or the orphans’ court; and

