1 (ii) Conduct hearings concerning such complaints, administer oaths
2 and affirmations, issue process to compel the attendance of witnesses and the production
3 of evidence, and require persons to testify and produce evidence by granting them immunity
4 from prosecution or from penalty or forfeiture.
5 (2) The Commission has the power to issue a reprimand and the power to
6 recommend to the Supreme Court of Maryland the removal, censure, or other appropriate
7 disciplining of a justice or judge or, in an appropriate case, retirement.
8 (3) All proceedings, testimony, and evidence before the Commission shall
9 be confidential and privileged, except as provided by rule of the Supreme Court of
10 Maryland; the record and any proceeding filed with the Supreme Court of Maryland shall
11 lose its confidential character, except as ordered by the Supreme Court of Maryland.
12 (4) No justice or judge shall participate as a member of the Commission in
13 any proceedings involving that justice’s or judge’s own conduct, and the Governor shall
14 appoint another justice or judge as a substitute member of the Commission for those
15 proceedings.
16 (5) (I) IN THE EVENT OF A MEMBER’S RECUSAL OR
17 DISQUALIFICATION OR THE EXPIRATION OF A MEMBER’S TERM WITHOUT A
18 REPLACEMENT, THE COMMISSION CHAIR MAY:
19 1. RECALL A FORMER MEMBER TO SERVE AS A
20 TEMPORARY SUBSTITUTE MEMBER; OR
21 2. REQUEST THAT THE GOVERNOR APPOINT A
22 TEMPORARY SUBSTITUTE MEMBER OR EXTEND A CURRENT MEMBER’S TERM.
23 (II) ON REQUEST OF THE COMMISSION CHAIR MADE UNDER
24 THIS PARAGRAPH, THE GOVERNOR MAY APPOINT A TEMPORARY SUBSTITUTE
25 MEMBER FOR A SPECIFIED PERIOD OR EXTEND A CURRENT MEMBER’S TERM UNTIL
26 A REPLACEMENT IS APPOINTED.
27 (III) ANY SUBSTITUTE MEMBER IS SUBJECT TO THE SAME
28 QUALIFICATIONS THAT WERE APPLICABLE TO THE MEMBER FOR WHOM THE
29 SUBSTITUTE IS TEMPORARILY APPOINTED.
30 (6) The Supreme Court of Maryland shall prescribe by rule the means to
31 implement and enforce the powers of the Commission and the practice and procedure before
32 the Commission.
33 (b) (1) Upon any recommendation of the Commission, the Supreme Court of
34 Maryland, after a hearing and upon a finding of misconduct while in office, or of persistent
35 failure to perform the duties of the office, or of conduct prejudicial to the proper

